uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-11-1x1.jpg 1w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-11-150x100.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-key-ingredients">Key Ingredients</h2>


<p>The ingredients are mostly pantry staples, so you can make it just about whenever the mood strikes! <em><a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#wprm-recipe-container-90865">Jump to the recipe</a> for measurements–this is just an overview.</em></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Chickpeas</strong>: We&#8217;re using two cans of chickpeas, or you can <a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/how-to-cook-dried-chickpeas/">cook your chickpeas from dried</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Garlic</strong>: Alright, garlic may not be the most romantic ingredient, but if you&#8217;re about to propose, we should be past the point of caring about garlic breath, right?</li>



<li><strong>Seasonings</strong>: Salt, oregano, crushed red pepper flakes, and black pepper bring flavor and spice!</li>



<li><strong>Sun-Dried Tomatoes</strong>: Bring that savory Tuscan flavor. Get the kind packed in oil!</li>



<li><strong>Broth</strong>: Vegetable broth, either from a carton, cube, or <a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/how-to-make-vegetable-broth/">homemade from veggie scraps</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Cream</strong>: In testing, I found heavy cream to give the best texture, but feel free to use half-and-half for a lighter dish, or coconut milk for a vegan option.</li>



<li><strong>Parmesan</strong>: Brings a savory taste perfect for rounding out this dish. Vegans should omit or use a plant-based parm.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1706" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201706'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Marry me chickpeas in a pan." class="wp-image-90858" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8.jpg 1200w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-400x569.jpg 400w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-211x300.jpg 211w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-768x1092.jpg 768w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-1080x1536.jpg 1080w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-650x924.jpg 650w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-42x60.jpg 42w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-1x1.jpg 1w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-150x213.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1706" src="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8.jpg" alt="Marry me chickpeas in a pan." class="wp-image-90858" srcset="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8.jpg 1200w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-400x569.jpg 400w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-211x300.jpg 211w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-768x1092.jpg 768w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-1080x1536.jpg 1080w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-650x924.jpg 650w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-42x60.jpg 42w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-1x1.jpg 1w, https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/marry-me-chickpeas-8-150x213.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-marry-me-chickpeas">How to make Marry Me Chickpeas</h2>


<p>Making this dish takes just 1 pan and less than 15 minutes. <em>This is an overview, <a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/marry-me-chickpeas/#wprm-recipe-container-90865">jump to the recipe</a> for the full printable recipe!</em></p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Make the flavor base</strong>, a delicious combination of butter, garlic, and spices.</li>



<li><strong>Add the fillings</strong> and cook for a few minutes.</li>



<li><strong>Finish</strong> it off with cream, parmesan, and basil!</li>
</ol>


<div class="block-tip-image cwp-inner">

<figure class="wp-block-image is-resized block-tip-image__image"><img width="548" height="548" decoding="async" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20548%20548'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" style="aspect-ratio:1;object-fit:cover;width:100;height:100" data-lazy-src="/wp-content/themes/liveeatlearn-2024/assets/images/sarahs-tip-circle.png"/><noscript><img width="548" height="548" decoding="async" src="/wp-content/themes/liveeatlearn-2024/assets/images/sarahs-tip-circle.png" alt="" style="aspect-ratio:1;object-fit:cover;width:100;height:100"/></noscript></figure>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading block-tip__title" id="h-i-like-adding-veggies">I like adding veggies</h2>


<p>While I absolutely love this dish just how it is, sometimes I&#8217;ll bulk it up with veggies! I&#8217;ll cook a bunch of <a href="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/how-to-air-fry-any-vegetable/">veggies in the air fryer</a> (zucchini and cauliflower are my favorites for this one), then stir them in right before serving.</p>

</div>


