	<h2 class="comments-title">507 Comments</h2><ol class="comment-list">	<li id="comment-199886" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent">
		<article id="div-comment-199886" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Lisa</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2026-01-10T12:18:37-07:00">January 10, 2026 at 12:18 pm</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>Would this recipe work in the instant pot? Any adjustments you’d recommend?</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-199886" data-commentid="199886" data-postid="90853" data-belowelement="div-comment-199886" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lisa" aria-label="Reply to Lisa">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li id="comment-200004" class="comment byuser comment-author-sarahlorrainebondgmail-com bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 staff">
		<article id="div-comment-200004" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Sarah Bond</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2026-01-12T15:17:42-07:00">January 12, 2026 at 3:17 pm</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I haven&#8217;t tested this one the Instant Pot so I really can&#8217;t say for sure but I think it would work. I would just add the basil, parmesan and cream after it has cooked.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

					</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-199908" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
		<article id="div-comment-199908" class="comment-body">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
										<b class="fn">Heather L</b> <span class="says">says:</span>				</div><!-- .comment-author -->

				<div class="comment-metadata">
					<time datetime="2026-01-10T14:44:52-07:00">January 10, 2026 at 2:44 pm</time>				</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
I&#8217;ve been wanting to make this for some time, and finally did tonight. It is delicious, and so easy. I&#8217;ve had a lot of chickpeas lately, so I did use white beans as suggested for an alternative.  I will say, if you are very sensitive to spice, maybe cut back on the red pepper flakes &#8211; definitely gave it a little kick. It was perfect for me, but I wouldn&#8217;t have wanted it any spicier. This is a keeper!</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-199908" data-commentid="199908" data-postid="90853" data-belowelement="div-comment-199908" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Heather L" aria-label="Reply to Heather L">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-199968" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
