							</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

			<div class="comment-content">
				<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
I have made this so many times and every time my family gets excited. This is a staple in our rotation, and I double it because everyone eats more than they usually do. It&#8217;s just that good. I puree the sundried tomatoes, so they really integrate and serve with some toasted crusty bread: *chef&#8217;s kiss*.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-200030" data-commentid="200030" data-postid="90853" data-belowelement="div-comment-200030" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Michelle Sanders" aria-label="Reply to Michelle Sanders">Reply</a></div>		</article><!-- .comment-body -->
